By Zhang Yue, Zhang Diyang, Jing Yibu, and Li Zailei, southern weekly reporters

Southern weekend intern, Wu Chao

Responsible Editor | Gu CE, Qian haoping

On the morning of March 9,2020, Zhu Heping, deputy director of Ophthalmology, lit a candle for the fourth time in the WECHAT circle of medical staff at Wuhan Central Hospital. He died of new pneumonia.

It was the third doctor to die of new coronary pneumonia in the hospital's ophthalmology department. The first two doctors were Mei Zhongming and Li Wenliang, whom former patients called "bright combination" . "those who were supposed to bring light to the patients are gone, " a doctor at the hospital told southern weekend.

March 1, the hospital thyroid breast surgery director Jiang Xueqing also died because of new pneumonia. He was also the only "major advanced model" to be named by the academy in the last year.

So far, four doctors have died at Wuhan Central Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The four doctors who died in the outbreak at Wuhan Central Hospital were deputy director of Ophthalmology, Mei Zhongming; ophthalmologist, Li Wenliang; deputy director of Ophthalmology, Zhu Heping; and Chief of Thyroid and breast surgery, Jiang Xueqing (from left to right) . (Ho Tsz / Photo)

Yang Er, a front-line doctor at the Central Hospital, told southern weekend that four doctors were still in danger. "I said they were in danger, not seriously ill, " he said, stressing that they were all multiple organ dysfunction syndrome, including respiratory failure, and accompanied by a variety of adverse complications, "some rely on external medical means to support life" .

He said the four endangered people are Vice President Wang Ping, Ethics Committee Liu Li (the hospital liver and gall bladder surgery director Cai Changchun's wife) , deputy chief of Thoracic Surgery Doctor Yi Fan, deputy chief of endocrinology Hu Weifeng.

As of February 9,68 confirmed cases had been reported among the staff and 266 medical personnel had been put under medical observation, according to a statement on the handling of the COVID-19 epidemic issued by the hospital's Public Health Department.

Two doctors at the hospital confirmed to southern weekend that they had seen the document among their colleagues.

According to public information, Wuhan Central Hospital staff infection in Wuhan is very prominent, medical deaths can be described as the most serious.

1
Hard to report

1

###Hard to report

Wuhan City Center Hospital was founded in 1880, formerly known as Hankou Catholic Hospital. It is one of the 28 Grade III, Class A hospital in Wuhan and is a public hospital in Wuhan. The hospital has three hospital districts, of which the Houhu Hospital district is the second batch of designated hospitals requisitioned by the Wuhan, and the Nanjing Road Hospital district later entered the list of designated hospitals.

At present, the hospital has more than 4300 employees, of which 1,206 are doctors and masters.

The Back Lake area of the Central Hospital is one of the closest hospitals to the south China Seafood Wholesale Market, 1.6 kilometers and a 23-minute walk. It's also where the new coronavirus first appeared.

According to the Covid-19, on the afternoon of December 29, the emergency physician notified the Public Health Department of four cases of south China Seafood Market, with abnormal conditions. The hospital called the Kong Hon Area Disease Control, but the other side said previously reported cases of similar cases have been tested for various pathogens, no results, need to report to the leadership.

Six days later, the district CDC still replied, "report it after the higher authorities have notified us, and report the specific diseases and other notifications. " Later, the hospital was again hit with a rubber ball about who to report to: The District Health Commission said it was a municipal hospital and reported it to the city; the City Health Commission said, territorial jurisdiction. report it to the district.

Since January 8, three days, finally reported 14 cases, but one of them can not be confirmed, the District Health Committee let contact the district disease control self-sampling, district disease control said and other district health committee notice. On the 13th, another patient can not sample the information reported to the CDC, the response is a word, "etc. . ".

From January 11 to 16, the hospital received reports of 26 suspected cases of infection among staff. According to Wuhan Health Commission notice, as of January 15, the city's medical staff zero infection.

Yang said many patients had no history of exposure to the south China seafood market since early January, but had clinical symptoms and imaging evidence. In addition, a succession of health care workers in contact with patients after the same symptoms. This is direct evidence of human-to-human transmission.

But when it came time to report the disease, they were told not to write "pneumonia of unknown origin" , or even "viral pneumonia" , but only "lung infection" . Lung infections are a very broad disease, he said, and do not highlight new infections or human-to-human transmission.

His colleagues confirmed that.

2
Secrets you can't tell me

2

###Secrets you can't tell me

What happened at the Central Hospital during the hard-to-report days?

One emergency physician was impressed by the end of December because the first cases were in the emergency department, Florida -- Several patients with cough, low fever, and Glassy Lung Ct.. When doctors sequenced the patients' Alveolar lavage fluid, the results were striking: "SARS coronavirus. ".

A screenshot of the test results was posted by Dr. Li Wenliang on the wechat group on Dec. 30,2019.

According to Ai, director of the hospital's emergency department, who had previously recalled to China Newsweek magazine, she received information from the hospital's Supervision Department about 0 p.m. on January 1,2020, and asked for a conversation the next day. In the course of the conversation, he was criticized for "being a professional with no principles and spreading rumors. Your irresponsible behavior has caused social panic and affected the development and stability of Wuhan" . Director Ai mentioned that the disease can be transmitted from person to person, but there was no response.

The emergency physician confirmed to reporters at southern weekend, "Director of the first time up the warning, 'SARS back' . But was reprimanded by the head of the institute, many people were present. She was reprimanded in three parallel sentences, to the effect that she was responsible for causing serious public opinion by publishing unverified news, which frightened my director

But Li Wenliang and AI were not the only ones called to talk, a doctor working in the hospital's medical imaging department told southern weekend. "A lot of people in our hospital were called in to talk and said nothing could be done. "

He and another doctor were later asked to delete the mournful pictures of Mei Zhongming and Li Wenliang that were published by the hospital. More than half of the more than 10 interviewees contacted by southern weekend said they had been subjected to intervention by the hospital, including admonishment, talks, being asked to delete the contents of the publication, being reminded by telephone not to release the relevant information, etc. .

A staff member in the back Lake area of the hospital remembers that, at that time, "let no publicity, materials even more dare not talk about. My hospital's many medical care is also infected at that time, heartache. At that time I was very desperate, especially desperate, no foreign aid, also do not let the report. ".

Two interviewees showed a screenshot of their wechat group to southern weekend reporters on December 30,2019, "please... don't release any information about pneumonia of unknown cause... or the Municipal Health Commission will seriously investigate and deal with it, " said the message, which was forwarded by Wuhan's Health Commission

Chen Xiaoning, a doctor at the hospital, told southern weekend that the early hospital unified requirements, "can not say, can not wear a mask, for fear of causing panic. "

Chen Xiaoning recalled, the outbreak began soon one day, near the end of work, hospital all the middle-level emergency meeting, oral communication, not to mention the word "coronavirus" , "control yourself, control your family. Chen Xiaoning, who had already left work that day, received a phone call from his leader and had to go back to the hospital to listen to the communication notice on the spot.

A number of central hospital staff confirmed to southern weekend reporters that they have received "can not say" , "can not wear a mask" these requirements, are conveyed orally layer by layer.

3
"make a fuss, disturb the morale of the troops"

3

###"make a fuss, disturb the morale of the troops"

At this time, only 2.6 kilometers away from the Central Hospital, almost at the same time found abnormal Hubei Province Integrated Hospital of Traditional Chinese and Western medicine, has been directly reported to the city and province. "On December 27, realizing that it might be contagious, the patients were isolated in single rooms and medical staff were instructed to take care of personal protection, " a source at the hospital told southern weekend

But Wuhan's Central Hospital, after the GAG, has failed to "tighten inside and tighten outside" and has not been reinforced.

Yang said that after being reported frequently at the end of December, the head of the hospital did not give any warning and did not in any way make people nervous. Even a department head wearing a mask to the meeting, but also criticized, "make a fuss, disturb the hearts of the army. ".

At the same time, the hospital leadership notice each department director, one by one call to inform each colleague, all must not leak any news of the virus, "I received that call. ".

Yang Er heard a number of colleagues mentioned that in early January, thyroid breast surgery director Jiang Xueqing to wear a mask to a meeting, was criticized by the hospital leadership. Since then, a number of doctors at the hospital have seen him without a mask. Unfortunately, a few days later, director Jiang was infected, diagnosed, then intubated, mechanically ventilated, ecmo, and gradually collapsed until death.

A doctor in the same department as Jiang Xueqing recalled to southern weekend reporters that Jiang had warned them "don't wear masks, it's bad for you. "

A screenshot of Jiang Xueqing's notebook appeared on the Internet, with notes from the meeting recorded: "unexplained viral pneumonia, no evidence of human-to-human transmission, ten rules of discipline, confidentiality, no talking nonsense... " 

Chen Xiaoning said that the notes are recorded in the January 3 meeting, the hospital organized a middle-level meeting, oral communication of the spirit, and oral communication to each employee.

Today, the Wechat Group, which has 87 members in its Jiang Xueqing section office, has replaced all the portraits with the same black-bottomed candles, leaving only a photo of Jiang Xueqing himself, who can no longer change his profile picture.

List of group members in director Jiang's department

Yu Lin is a retired employee of the Central Hospital. She recalled that the last time she saw director Jiang was on the afternoon of January 13, when he was still at the specialist clinic.

Director Jiang said to her, "big sister, what are you doing here? Here is very dangerous, you do things quickly go. " Said this time, he was surrounded by patients, no mask.

Southern weekend reporters received a "January 13 viral pneumonia related situation report (Nanjing Road) " from a central hospital doctor. The Nanjing Road Hospital district monitored 85 medical personnel in close contact that day, there were 9 fever outpatients, 29 in isolation ward, 34 in aspiration department and 13 in Ophthalmology Department.

The Ophthalmology Department, which is supposed to be far away from the respiratory disease, has suffered the most casualties of the outbreak.

According to the report, on January 10, an eye patient was transferred to the isolation ward. On January 11, Li Wenliang, a tube bed doctor, reported a fever of 37.2 C. On the morning of the 12th, another ophthalmologist reported a fever of 37.4 C, after which he developed the same symptoms as Li Wenliang.

Chen Xiaoning said that before, the Department of Ophthalmology required the equipment department and the hospital sense office to give corresponding materials to protect the medical staff, but the hospital sense office director at that time only gave the first-level protection, "the first-level protection is the worst, and the third-level protection is the best. ".

Zhu Heping, the deputy director of Ophthalmology who died on March 9, was a hospital rehire specialist who had retired. Chen Xiaoning said, Dr. Zhu is a very good person, after the infection, his wife and daughter are not around, a person at home for more than 10 days, was 120 to the hospital, did not find anyone to help.

Despite the deaths of four medical staff members, only two doctors, Jiang Xueqing and Mei Zhongming, had their obituaries published on the wechat public account of Wuhan's Central Hospital. Both doctors'obituaries were issued three hours after their deaths, but Dr. Zhu, who has been dead for more than 24 hours, still has no obituaries.

Southern weekend reporter calls the Public Health section of this hospital for this, the other side replies please contact propaganda section.

4
Supplies are running out

4

###Supplies are running out

The departments of critical care and deceased doctors in the Central Hospital are: Ophthalmology, thyroid and breast surgery, digestive medicine, cardiac surgery, urology, Otolaryngology, ethics, etc. , there was no direct correlation between the prevalence of NCP and the treatment of NCP.

"They didn't even have time to go to the front to fight the virus, " Yang said. The cause of the collapse was a lack of early warning and poor protective equipment.

He recalled that on January 23, the hospital is in dire need of supplies, everyone to the name of personal assistance, was blocked by the hospital, not private fundraising. Later, when the situation was pressing, donations could be raised, but the distribution of goods and materials was in chaos. For example, things that had been brought in could not be collected, people who had been handed over disappeared, and even the materials that had been brought in were not wanted.

There was a group of doctors in the hospital, more than 300 people, who were in charge of matching donations. Southern weekend reporters saw the chat record, February 10, a colleague in the group said, contact a thousand pounds of rice, "the hospital did not even want. ".

Earlier, the hospital had been "out of food. ". 2,000 people in a typical cafeteria, two meals a day. In Times of crisis, doctors and patients live and eat in hospitals, cooking meals for 6,000 people three times a day, and are temporarily undersupplied. January 26 or so, many medical staff by eating snacks to adhere to, some departments "food" for a day, some for three days.

What is even more lacking is protective materials, especially protective clothing.

In mid-february, the topic of discussion on the Wechat group was how to transform raincoats into protective clothing. "It is said that water splashing is not a problem, but depends on the permeability of the materials, " and doctors designed a "raincoat disinfection program. ".

"I was out of food and ammunition for a while, and I had everything I could wear. " For a while, Yang Er took the family's garbage bag to the hospital to use as a raincoat and wrapped it around his hands, feet and neck. This problem was not solved until the field resumed work and the field medical team entered the hospital.

Yang Er often goes to the hospital locker where he keeps his protective suit. Before late February, the six-layer metal cabinet was always half empty or empty.

He sent a photo of a colleague wearing a protective suit at the time, thin as a Gossamer, "it's just streaking, it's really a death squad. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At one point, doctors at the Central Hospital were wearing "thin as a Gossamer" protective clothing (photo / photo by interviewees) 

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As of February 29,158,000 masks and 3,976 protective clothing had been donated to the Wuhan Central Hospital by five major state-run charities, according to southern weekend. This was donated throughout the outbreak, and official donations of protective clothing were not enough for the entire hospital to use once.

During the interview, six doctors from different departments confirmed to the southern weekend reporter that the materials were running out.

In the beginning, there was little quarantine, Ms. Chen said. The back office, for example, has a floor with fewer than 100 workers. Three people were infected years ago. The building is still air conditioning. "There are no windows, no ventilation, no sterilization. ".

"The academy does not speak either, nor does the academy leadership. "

He remembers making rounds on New Year's Eve, no shoe covers, garbage bags for his feet. When masks are most in short supply, wear an industrial N95 under and a surgical mask over it. As for the administrative staff, do not belong to the first line, received a box of masks after nothing, go to work mask is their own to find people to buy.

On January 23rd, February 6th, February 14th, Wuhan Central Hospital has issued a notice to solicit donations of protective materials. On February 14, Cai Yifawen, head of the hospital's pain department, called attention to the shortage of medical personnel in Wuhan.

A ICU nurse in the Nanjing Road Hospital district said that only after the Union Medical College and Tongji Hospital began to openly solicit donations did other hospitals dare to post because the two hospitals are provincial hospitals. Similarly, the protection is, "our hospital is to see Tongji protection after the dare to protect" , at first protective clothing not to wear, for fear of causing tension.

An ultrasound doctor, who volunteers as a liaison material, told southern weekend that a notice was issued on February 19 saying donations could be accepted before cash was allowed.

"after the Spring Festival, many manufacturers selling protective products have resumed their work, but it is still very difficult for us to purchase materials ourselves. We have to look for donations first, and then go shopping. "

Two other doctors said there were also problems with subsidies for front-line care, and that the January hospital benefit had not yet been received. As a first-line staff, there is a one-time 6000 yuan subsidies, as well as 200 yuan or 300 yuan per day subsidies, night shift fees 180 yuan.

The above-mentioned nurse in ICU of Nanjing Road Hospital district said that after her minimum wage was deducted, only 1000 yuan was less than 1,000 yuan, and the January allowance had not been paid. But at his own expense, he bought 180 approved masks from the United States and spent more than 2,000 yuan on them. I don't know if he will receive them.

As of February 29, five official charities had allocated 123 million yuan to the central hospital, according to southern weekend.

Several doctors said the shortages were not resolved until late February, when outside rescue teams arrived.

Gansu Medical Team 105 People Assistance Center Hospital, one of the doctors told southern weekend reporters, in early February, the main problem here is that there are many patients, protective supplies shortage, can not reach the three-level protection, into the isolation ward there is no N95. "The hospital is not well managed. We don't have much to bring. It's all going to the Central Hospital. "

5
"It's like a train station during the Spring Festival. "

5

###"It's like a train station during the Spring Festival. "

Another factor contributing to the deaths and injuries was the lack of proper quarantine.

As one of the same designated hospitals, the deputy director of the Wuchang Hospital told southern weekend that after the hospital was designated as a designated hospital, the director, Liu Zhiming, specifically asked the city's disease control experts to guide the isolation measures for ward renovation. At that time, Liu Zhiming often went to the ward and outpatient visits, later infected, and died on February 18.

The Central Hospital has taken on a great deal of relief work since the beginning of the epidemic, a doctor said, "When we first opened more than 700 beds in Jinyintan Hospital, our hospital also opened more than 500 beds directly. At that time, all kinds of work had not been put in place before opening, and the quarantine area and the contaminated area had not been well developed. "

Another doctor sent a picture of the patient and medical staff in the hall separated only by a propaganda board, not separated from the top, the effect of isolation.

Yang Er remembers, January 6 or so, the hospital vacates two wards to do the isolation ward, adds up to also only a few dozen beds, far from enough. In the end, more than 600 beds were rebuilt in the Houhu district, which was still overcrowded.

"In January, it was like a train station during the Spring Festival. Patients were lining up, falling down. At least three of my colleagues were being pulled, ripped, and threatened to kill their doctors by impatient patients. "

"I don't judge [ some ] hospital leaders, " said one Houhu district doctor. "Our head nurse, head nurse, department head, I'll give a thumbs-up, including the vice-head. Anyway, our clinical people are very united. "

In fact, many interviewees expressed their dissatisfaction with the secretary and the president. One doctor said they lacked clinical experience. "One of them was a teacher, the other was a health official, " others said, "There is official authority" "don't say anything (new Crown Virus) , which said on the blame" "other people put forward opinions, also don't let say, don't take seriously, make our underlings indignant. "

Many of the doctors interviewed miss the former President Xia Jiahong, a clinician from the background, know grass-roots suffering, often in the night shift "incognito private visit. ". "Once, he saw the night shift doctor spend an hour or so sorting the test sheets, and he spent a lot of money to go online paperless to solve the problem, " said one of the doctors interviewed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hospital leaders take photos of hospital staff visiting infected patients on March 8(photo / Photo of interviewees)

Jring, a retired staff member of the hospital, said he regretted that the incident had damaged the hospital. "A good hospital with a history of more than 100 years, the staff and staff are very distressed. When the epidemic is over, they will have to go to the hospital to ask for explanation. "

In Yang Er's mind, the end of January and the beginning of February are the "darkest hours" of this hospital. Here, he said, a lot of people put up with it. But some colleagues said that after the epidemic, to change careers.

He says many of his colleagues are more dedicated and inspiring than he is. One of his colleagues, three people in the family have died because of new coronary pneumonia, GRANDPA, grandma and GRANDPA, she could not give the family in his hospital to find a bed, but still work every day to save people, did not ask for leave.

Asked why he had come out to speak, he said, "every man is responsible for the rise and fall of his country. "

(at the request of the interviewee, Yang Er, Chen Xiaoning and Yu Lin were given pseudonyms. Public Name Author Zhang Beihai is also helpful.)
